As a book club selection, I was compelled to finish reading it. I would not have otherwise. The. weaving of E.B. White's experiences and history with author's did not result in either a clear portrait or an empathetic feeling for either author. This reader was left with distaste for falconry as practiced by both authors. The nature of the bird, its necessity to hunt, and man's harnessing of its power certainly had some positive purpose historically. Unfortunately, the memoir fails to convey it
